.nh
.TH "BCDOCK" "1" "Jan 2025" "BCDock CLI" "BCDock Manual"

.SH NAME
bcdock-al - Compile AL projects using the alc that matches the target BC env


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBbcdock al [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Run alc.exe versioned to a specific BC environment, by extracting the
ALLanguage.vsix that BcContainerHelper bundled with that env's BC platform.

.PP
The vsix is served anonymously by every BC container on its downloads endpoint
(env.downloadsUrl/ALLanguage.vsix) - same binary BcContainerHelper unpacks
during container setup, so it's always version-matched to the env's platform.

.PP
Exit codes:
  0   ok
  1   general error


.SH OPTIONS
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for al


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--api-url\fP=""
	API base URL (env: BCDOCK_API_URL)

.PP
\fB--no-color\fP[=false]
	Disable colored output

.PP
\fB-o\fP, \fB--output\fP="table"
	Output format: table, json, csv

.PP
\fB-q\fP, \fB--quiet\fP[=false]
	Suppress non-essential output

.PP
\fB--timeout\fP=30s
	Request timeout

.PP
\fB--token\fP=""
	API token (env: BCDOCK_TOKEN)


.SH EXAMPLE
.EX
  bcdock al compile --env my-env
.EE


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBbcdock(1)\fP, \fBbcdock-al-compile(1)\fP
